2), pp. 141-158; Howald, G., Al, E., Invasive rodent eradication on islands (2007) Conserv. Biol., 21 (5), pp. 1258-1268; Howarth, F.G., Environmental impacts of classical biological control (1991) Ann. Rev. Entomol., 36 (1), pp. 485-509; Huettl, R.F., Liming and fertilization as mitigation tools in declining forest ecosystems (1989) Water. Air Soil Pollut., 44 (1-2), pp. 93-118; Jacob, J., Singleton, G.R., Hinds, L.A., Fertility control of rodent pests (2008) Wildl. Res., 35 (6), pp. 487-493; Keith, D.W., Geoengineering the climate: History and prospect (2000) Ann. Rev. Energy Environ., 25 (1), pp. 245-284; Keith, D.W., (2001) Encyclopedia of Global Change; Keith, D.W., (2009) Climate Change Science and Policy; Kellogg, W.W., Schneider, S.H., Climate stabilization: For better of worse? (1974) Science, 186 (4170), pp. 1163-1172; Lampo, M., De Leo, G.A., The invasion ecology of the toad Bufo marinus: From South America to Australia (1998) Ecol. Appl., 8, pp. 388-396; Marchetti, C., On geoengineering and the CO2 problem (1977) Clim. Change, 1 (1), pp. 59-68; Matthews, H.D., Cao, L., Caldeira, K., Sensitivity of ocean acidification to geoengineered climate stabilization (2009) Geophys. Res. Lett., 36 (10), p. 10706; McCallum, H., Immunocontraception for wildlife population control (1996) Trends Ecol. Evol., 11 (12), pp. 491-493; Minckley, W.L., Translocation as a tool for conserving imperiled fishes: Experiences in Western United States (1995) Biol. Conserv., 72 (2), pp. 297-309; Moore, S.A., Al, E., Diversity in current ecological thinking: Implications for environmental management (2009) Environ. Manage., 43 (1), pp. 17-27; Morley, C.G., Has the invasive mongoose Herpestes javanicus yet reached the island of Taveuni, Fiji (2004) Oryx, 38 (4), pp. 457-460; Myers, J.H., Simberloff, D., Kuris, A.M., Carey, J.R., Eradication revisited: Dealing with exotic species (2000) Trends Ecol. Evol., 15 (8), pp. 316-320; (1992) Policy Implications of Greenhouse Warming: Mitigation 